ui.calibration.compass_prompt: Select OK to begin calibration. You must be in space and have the compass visible.

ui.status.label: Status: {status}
ui.message.reset_waypoint_body: After resetting the Waypoint List, the Waypoint Assist will start again from the first point in the list at the next start.
ui.message.reset_waypoint_error_body: Waypoint Assist must be disabled before you can reset the list.
ui.message.invalid_float_body: Veuillez saisir des valeurs numériques valides.
ui.tooltip.mode.fsd_route:
Will execute your route.
At each jump the sequence will perform some fuel scooping.
ui.tooltip.mode.supercruise:
Will keep your ship pointed to target,
your target can only be a station for the autodocking to work.
ui.tooltip.mode.waypoint:
When selected, will prompt for the waypoint file.
The waypoint file contains System names that
will be entered into Galaxy Map and route plotted.
ui.tooltip.mode.dss: When selected, will perform DSS scans while you are traveling between stars.
ui.tooltip.mode.elw_scanner:
Will perform FSS scans while FSD Assist is traveling between stars.
If the FSS shows a signal in the region of Earth,
Water or Ammonia type worlds, it will announce that discovery.
ui.tooltip.mode.afk_combat: Used with a AFK Combat ship in a Rez Zone.
ui.tooltip.ship.roll_rate: Roll rate your ship has in deg/sec. Higher the number the more maneuverable the ship.
ui.tooltip.ship.pitch_rate: Pitch (up/down) rate your ship has in deg/sec. Higher the number the more maneuverable the ship.
ui.tooltip.ship.yaw_rate: Yaw rate (rudder) your ship has in deg/sec. Higher the number the more maneuverable the ship.
ui.tooltip.ship.sun_pitch_time:
This field is for ships that tend to overheat.
Providing 1-2 more seconds of Pitch up when avoiding the Sun
will overcome this problem.
ui.tooltip.autopilot.sun_bright_threshol:
The low level for brightness detection,
range 0-255, want to mask out darker items
ui.tooltip.autopilot.nav_align_tries: How many attempts the ap should make at alignment.
ui.tooltip.autopilot.jump_tries: How many attempts the ap should make to jump.
ui.tooltip.autopilot.docking_retries: How many attempts to make to dock.
ui.tooltip.autopilot.wait_for_autodock:
After docking granted,
wait this amount of time for us to get docked with autodocking
ui.tooltip.buttons.start_fsd: Button to start FSD route assist.
ui.tooltip.fuel.refuel_threshold:
If fuel level get below this level,
it will attempt refuel.
ui.tooltip.fuel.scoop_timeout:
Number of second to wait for full tank,
might mean we are not scooping well or got a small scooper
ui.tooltip.fuel.fuel_threshold_abort:
Level at which AP will terminate,
because we are not scooping well.
ui.tooltip.overlay.x_offset: Offset left the screen to start place overlay text.
ui.tooltip.overlay.y_offset: Offset down the screen to start place overlay text.
ui.tooltip.calibrate:
Will iterate through a set of scaling values
getting the best match for your system.
See HOWTO-Calibrate.md
ui.tooltip.waypoint.button: Read in a file with with your Waypoints.
ui.tooltip.waypoint.cap_mouse:
This will provide the StationCoord value of the Station in the SystemMap.
Selecting this button and then clicking on the Station in the SystemMap
will return the x,y value that can be pasted in the waypoints file
ui.tooltip.waypoint.reset:
Reset your waypoint list,
the waypoint assist will start again at the first point in the list.
